1D ising model w periodic boundary conditions

the system is eveolved by random attempts to flip spins until the system convereges to equilibrium near a free energy minimum. This is done using Monte Carlo steps (i.e. random spin flips) and accepting the attempts using Metropolis criterion

Open Ising1d.c++ w text editor and explore

to run type

./bash.run.sh

from terminal.

Note. You need gnuplot installed to generate the movie gif.
